'''反老藥'''（Senolytic）是一類受到基礎科學研究以確定其是否能選擇性地殺死[[細胞衰老|衰老細胞]]並增進人體健康的[[小分子|小分子]]物質；<ref name="pmid26646499">{{cite journal |last1=Childs |first1=Bennett G |last2=Durik |first2=Matej |last3=Baker |first3=Darren J |last4=van Deursen |first4=Jan M |title=Cellular senescence in aging and age-related disease: from mechanisms to therapy |journal=Nature Medicine |date=8 December 2015 |volume=21 |issue=12 |pages=1424–1435 |doi=10.1038/nm.4000 |pmid=26646499 |pmc=4748967 }}</ref>這類研究的目標是找出或開發能延緩、阻止、紓解甚至逆轉老化相關疾病的藥物。<ref name="pmid25446976">{{cite journal |last1=Kirkland |first1=James L. |last2=Tchkonia |first2=Tamara |title=Clinical strategies and animal models for developing senolytic agents |journal=Experimental Gerontology |date=August 2015 |volume=68 |pages=19–25 |doi=10.1016/j.exger.2014.10.012 |pmid=25446976 |pmc=4412760 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=van Deursen |first1=Jan M. |title=Senolytic therapies for healthy longevity |journal=Science |date=16 May 2019 |volume=364 |issue=6441 |pages=636–637 |doi=10.1126/science.aaw1299 |pmid=31097655 |pmc=6816502 |bibcode=2019Sci...364..636V }}</ref>與此類研究相關的一個概念是「凍齡」（senostatic），其意為抑制老化。

==研究==
目前對返老藥的研究處於初步階段，其中一些已經進入人體試驗階段的早期。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Baumann |first1=Kim |title=Rejuvenating senolytics |journal=Nature Reviews Molecular Cell Biology |date=27 July 2018 |volume=19 |issue=9 |pages=543 |doi=10.1038/s41580-018-0047-5 |pmid=30054558 |url=https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/b6ac926fffc74b0b4b2180108aa41399cb91e9a1 }}</ref>目前多數潛在的返老藥，其原本的目的是用作抗癌藥物，像是用於[[化療|化療]]的藥物[[达沙替尼|达沙替尼]]以及實驗性的小分子藥物那維托克（Navitoclax，ABT-263）等是其中的例子。<ref name="pmid24345884">{{cite journal |last1=Blagosklonny |first1=Mikhail V |title=Selective anti-cancer agents as anti-aging drugs |journal=Cancer Biology & Therapy |date=28 October 2014 |volume=14 |issue=12 |pages=1092–1097 |doi=10.4161/cbt.27350 |pmid=24345884 |pmc=3912031 }}</ref><ref name="pmid26587873">{{cite journal |last1=Slack |first1=Cathy |last2=Alic |first2=Nazif |last3=Partridge |first3=Linda |title=Could cancer drugs provide ammunition against aging? |journal=Cell Cycle |date=6 January 2016 |volume=15 |issue=2 |pages=153–155 |doi=10.1080/15384101.2015.1118905 |pmid=26587873 |pmc=4825846 }}</ref>

